name: Dead Fish Handshake - The Sixes (CD)
description:
1. Turning a Blind Eye
2. E-Motionless
3. Recquiescat
4. The Blackest Skies
5. Lifespan
6. Leave The Light On

Produced by Clint Lowery
Mixed by Mike Ferretti
Engineered by Mike Ferretti
Assistant Engineer: Johnny Fantozzi
Recorded and Mixed at Architekt Studios in Butler, New Jersey
Mastered by Alan Douches at West West Side Music in New Windsor, New York
Album Artwork & Design: Paul Guzzo

"The Sixes" is Dead Fish Handshake's second record. 
Produced by Sevendust guitarist, Clint Lowery, this new collection of songs takes the DFH sound to the next level. The band co-wrote with Clint Lowery as well as penning a song with he and Morgan Rose (Sevendust) as well. The lead single, "Turning a Blind Eye" has been sent to radio. Please request it!

Additional Musicians:
Clint Lowery: guitar [E-Motionless, Lifespan], vocals [The Blackest Skies]
Kurt Wubbenhorst: programming

name: Dead Fish Handshake - Across State Lines (CD)
description:
1. Undercurrent
2. Safe Place
3. Changes
4. No Tomorrow
5. Black and Blue
6. I Know

Produced by: Rob Ferreira
Co-produced by Dead Fish Handshake
Recorded at Home Sweet Studios, Linden, NJ by: Rob Ferreira
Mixed at Suburban Soul Studios, Torrance, CA by: Charlie Park
Mastered at Spectre Mastering, Renton, WA by: Troy Glessner
Photography & artwork: Paul Guzzo

“Across State Lines” is the debut record by Dead Fish Handshake, a rock band based out of the Northeast United States. Slated for a March 5th, 2011 release, the six song collection ranges from the guitar driven riff rock of “Undercurrent” to the ballad-esque melodies of “Changes” and “I Know”. The release will be available through online digital retailers as well as physical CD via www.deadfishhandshake.com and on tour-dates.

The foursome has road tested the material playing the club, college and festival circuit as well as opening for a national act on more than one occasion.

This introduction to the DFH sound, produced by guitarist Rob Ferreira, boasts guest performances by a handful of talented musicians from the NJ area in an effort to feature one of the more promising local scenes on the East Coast.

"...great riffs and near perfect arrangements with hooks that you won’t be able to get out of your heads" – The Aquarian.
